NAME
	video-pane (display) - render a decoded video feed from a vid9p stream directory, compositing I420 frames through the mpeg remap24 path into the pane

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	<mount>/fmt	"<w> <h> i420 <fps>" — stream geometry.
	<mount>/frame	the I420 byte stream; each w*h*3/2 bytes is one
			decoded frame (see appl/cmd/vid9p.b).

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	The mount path is a vid9p stream directory (e.g. /mnt/video/0)
	served by appl/cmd/vid9p.b over the host-decode 9P bridge
	(docs/H264-9P-BRIDGE.md).  fmt is read once for geometry; frames
	are fetched by index with pread (the frame file is random
	access), wrapped as a Mpegio->YCbCr and run through the SAME
	remap24 (YCbCr->RGB24) converter the standalone vidplay/vidplay9p
	players use — there is no new pixel code.  The frame is drawn at
	its native size, centred in the pane and clipped to the pane
	rectangle, with a transport status strip along the bottom edge.

	The pane is a transport-controlled player.  It exports the
	optional MatrixTicker interface (matrix.m), so the runtime calls
	update() at frame cadence; playback paces itself against the
	wall clock at the feed's fps.  Keys, routed by Matrix to the
	focused (hovered) pane:

	space	play / pause
	s	stop: canned feed rewinds to frame 0, paused; a live
		feed snaps back to the live edge, playing
	arrows	seek 5 s back / forward; on a live feed, seeking back
		replays the retained buffer (DVR) and seeking to the
		end resumes following the live edge

	A canned clip loops at end of stream; a live (streaming) feed
	follows the newest decoded frame.  fmt/frame need not exist at
	init: the pane retries lazily and shows "no video" until the
	source appears.  Multiplex by placing one video-pane leaf per
	feed in the composition (see the video-player and video-live
	crystallisations in /lib/matrix/compositions).

SEE ALSO
	vid9p (appl/cmd/vid9p.b — serves /mnt/video/<id>)
	vidplay9p (appl/mpeg — standalone windowed player, same feed)
	docs/H264-9P-BRIDGE.md, docs/MULTIPLEXED-VIDEO-SPIKE.md
